<h1>Feats</h1>

<h2 id=3D"prerequisites">Prerequisites</h2>
<p>
	Some feats have prerequisites. Your character must have the indicated abil=
ity score, class feature, feat, skill, base attack bonus, or other quality =
designated in order to select or use that feat. A character can gain a feat=
 at the same level at which he or she gains the prerequisite.
</p>
<p>
	A character can=E2=80=99t use a feat if he or she has lost a prerequisite.
</p>

<h2 id=3D"typesOfFeats">Types Of Feats</h2>
<p>
	Some feats are general, meaning that no special rules govern them as a gro=
up. Others are item creation feats, which allow spellcasters to create magi=
c items of all sorts. A metamagic feat lets a spellcaster prepare and cast =
a spell with greater effect, albeit as if the spell were a higher spell lev=
el than it actually is.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"fighterBonusFeats">Fighter Bonus Feats</h3>
<p>
	Any feat designated as a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fig=
hter.htm">fighter</a> feat can be selected as a fighter=E2=80=99s bonus fea=
t. This designation does not restrict characters of other classes from sele=
cting these feats, assuming that they meet any prerequisites.
</p>
