<h3 id=3D"improvedFamiliar">Improved Familiar [General]</h3>
<p>
	This feat allows spellcasters to acquire a new <a href=3D"https://www.d20s=
rd.org/srd/classes/sorcererWizard.htm#familiars">familiar</a> from a nonsta=
ndard list, but only when they could normally acquire a new familiar.
</p>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Ability to acquire a new familiar, compatible <a href=3D"https://www.d20sr=
d.org/srd/description.htm#alignment">alignment</a>, sufficiently high level=
 (see below).
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When choosing a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/sorcererWiza=
rd.htm#familiars">familiar</a>, the creatures listed below are also availab=
le to the spellcaster. The spellcaster may choose a familiar with an <a hre=
f=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/description.htm#alignment">alignment</a> up=
 to one step away on each of the alignment axes (lawful through chaotic, go=
od through evil).
</p>

<p>
	Improved familiars otherwise use the rules for regular familiars, with two=
 exceptions: If the creature=E2=80=99s type is something other than animal,=
 its type does not change; and improved familiars do not gain the ability t=
o speak with other creatures of their kind (although many of them already h=
ave the ability to communicate).
</p>
<p>
	The list in <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#tableImprovedF=
amiliarbyAlignment">Table: Improved Familiar by Alignment</a> presents only=
 a few possible improved familiars. Almost any creature of the same general=
 size and power as those on the list makes a suitable familiar. Nor is the =
master=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/description.htm#alig=
nment">alignment</a> the only possible categorization. For instance, improv=
ed familiars could be assigned by the master=E2=80=99s creature type or sub=
type, as shown in <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#tableImpr=
ovedFamiliarbyTypeSubtype">Table: Improved Familiar by Type/Subtype</a>.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedFeint">Improved Feint [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Int 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#combatExpertise">C=
ombat Expertise</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You can make a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/bluff.htm">Blu=
ff</a> check to <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks=
.htm#feint">feint</a> in combat as a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
combat/actionsInCombat.htm#moveActions">move action</a>.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#feint">Fei=
nting</a> in combat is a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/actio=
nsInCombat.htm#standardActions">standard action</a>.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Feint as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedGrapple">Improved Grapple [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Dex 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#improvedUnarmedStr=
ike">Improved Unarmed Strike</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You do not provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/attacks=
OfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> when you make a <a href=3D"htt=
ps://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#touchAttacks">touch att=
ack</a> to start a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAtta=
cks.htm#grapple">grapple</a>. You also gain a +4 bonus on all <a href=3D"ht=
tps://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#grappleChecks">grapple c=
hecks</a>, regardless of whether you started the grapple.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/co=
mbat/attacksOfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> when you make a <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#touchAttack=
s">touch attack</a> to start a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat=
/specialAttacks.htm#grapple">grapple</a>.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Grapple as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/monk.htm">monk</a> may sel=
ect Improved Grapple as a bonus feat at 1st level, even if she does not mee=
t the prerequisites.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedInitiative">Improved Initiative [General]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You get a +4 bonus on initiative checks.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Initiative as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedOverrun">Improved Overrun [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Str 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#powerAttack">Power=
 Attack</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When you attempt to <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAt=
tacks.htm#overrun">overrun</a> an opponent, the target may not choose to av=
oid you. You also gain a +4 bonus on your Strength check to knock down your=
 opponent.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, the target of an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
combat/specialAttacks.htm#overrun">overrun</a> can choose to avoid you or t=
o block you.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Overrun as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedPreciseShot">Improved Precise Shot [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Dex 19, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#pointBlankShot">Po=
int Blank Shot</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#precise=
Shot">Precise Shot</a>, base attack bonus +11.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	Your ranged attacks ignore the AC bonus granted to targets by anything les=
s than <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatModifiers.htm#tot=
alCover">total cover</a>, and the miss chance granted to targets by anythin=
g less than <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatModifiers.ht=
m#totalConcealment">total concealment</a>. Total cover and total concealmen=
t provide their normal benefits against your ranged attacks.
</p>
<p>
	In addition, when you shoot or throw ranged weapons at a <a href=3D"https:=
//www.d20srd.org/srd/conditionSummary.htm#grappling">grappling</a> opponent=
, you automatically strike at the opponent you have chosen.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	See the normal rules on the effects of <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/s=
rd/combat/combatModifiers.htm#cover">cover</a> and <a href=3D"https://www.d=
20srd.org/srd/combat/combatModifiers.htm#concealment">concealment</a>. With=
out this feat, a character who shoots or throws a ranged weapon at a target=
 involved in a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.=
htm#grapple">grapple</a> must roll randomly to see which grappling combatan=
t the attack strikes.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Precise Shot as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>
<p>
	An 11th-level <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm">ra=
nger</a> who has chosen the archery combat style is treated as having Impro=
ved Precise Shot, even if he does not have the prerequisites for it, but on=
ly when he is wearing light or no armor.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedShieldBash">Improved Shield Bash [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisite</h5>
<p>
	<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#shieldProficiency">Shield =
Proficiency</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When you perform a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAtt=
acks.htm#shieldBashAttacks">shield bash</a>, you may still apply the shield=
=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/theBasics.htm#shieldBonus"=
>shield bonus</a> to your AC.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, a character who performs a <a href=3D"https://www.d20sr=
d.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#shieldBashAttacks">shield bash</a> lose=
s the shield=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/theBasics.htm#=
shieldBonus">shield bonus</a> to AC until his or her next turn.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Shield Bash as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedSunder">Improved Sunder [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Str 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#powerAttack">Power=
 Attack</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When you <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#s=
under">strike at an object held or carried by an opponent</a> (such as a we=
apon or shield), you do not provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/sr=
d/combat/attacksOfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a>.
</p>
<p>
	You also gain a +4 bonus on any <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/comb=
at/combatStatistics.htm#attackRoll">attack roll</a> made to attack an objec=
t held or carried by another character.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/co=
mbat/attacksOfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> when you strike at=
 an object held or carried by another character.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Sunder as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedTrip">Improved Trip [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Int 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#combatExpertise">C=
ombat Expertise</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You do not provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/attacks=
OfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> when you attempt to <a href=3D=
"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#trip">trip</a> an opp=
onent while you are unarmed. You also gain a +4 bonus on your Strength chec=
k to trip your opponent.
</p>
<p>
	If you trip an opponent in melee combat, you immediately get a melee attac=
k against that opponent as if you hadn=E2=80=99t used your attack for the t=
rip attempt.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you provoke an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/co=
mbat/attacksOfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> when you attempt t=
o <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#trip">tri=
p</a> an opponent while you are unarmed.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	At 6th level, a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/monk.htm">mo=
nk</a> may select Improved Trip as a bonus feat, even if she does not have =
the prerequisites.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Trip as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedTurning">Improved Turning [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisite</h5>
<p>
	Ability to turn or rebuke creatures.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You turn or rebuke creatures as if you were one level higher than you are =
in the class that grants you the ability.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedTwoWeaponFighting">Improved Two-Weapon Fighting [General]=
</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Dex 17, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#twoWeaponFighting"=
>Two-Weapon Fighting</a>, base attack bonus +6.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	In addition to the standard single extra attack you get with an off-hand w=
eapon, you get a second attack with it, albeit at a -5 penalty.  See the <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#twoWeaponFigh=
ting">Two-Weapon Fighting</a> special attack.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you can only get a single extra attack with an off-hand=
 weapon.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Two-Weapon Fighting as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>
<p>
	A 6th-level <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm">rang=
er</a> who has chosen the two-weapon combat style is treated as having Impr=
oved Two-Weapon Fighting, even if he does not have the prerequisites for it=
, but only when he is wearing light or no armor.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"improvedUnarmedStrike">Improved Unarmed Strike [General]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You are considered to be armed even when unarmed =E2=80=94that is, you do =
not provoke attacks or opportunity from armed opponents when you attack the=
m while unarmed. However, you still get an <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.or=
g/srd/combat/attacksOfOpportunity.htm">attack of opportunity</a> against an=
y opponent who makes an unarmed attack on you.
</p>
<p>
	In addition, your <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapons.=
htm#unarmedStrike">unarmed strikes</a> can deal lethal or <a href=3D"https:=
//www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/injuryandDeath.htm#nonlethalDamage">nonlethal d=
amage</a>, at your option.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you are considered unarmed when attacking with an <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapons.htm#unarmedStrike">unarm=
ed strike</a>, and you can deal only <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/=
combat/injuryandDeath.htm#nonlethalDamage">nonlethal damage</a> with such a=
n attack.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/monk.htm">monk</a> automat=
ically gains Improved Unarmed Strike as a bonus feat at 1st level. She need=
 not select it.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Improved Unarmed Strike as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"investigator">Investigator [General]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You get a +2 bonus on all <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/gat=
herInformation.htm">Gather Information</a> checks and <a href=3D"https://ww=
w.d20srd.org/srd/skills/search.htm">Search</a> checks.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"ironWill">Iron Will [General]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You get a +2 bonus on all <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/com=
batStatistics.htm#reflex">Will saving throws</a>.
</p>

