	Dex 13, Wis 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#improvedUn=
armedStrike">Improved Unarmed Strike</a>, base attack bonus +8.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You must declare that you are using this feat before you make your <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#attackRoll">atta=
ck roll</a> (thus, a failed attack roll ruins the attempt). Stunning Fist f=
orces a foe damaged by your unarmed attack to make a <a href=3D"https://www=
.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#fortitude">Fortitude saving thr=
ow</a> (DC 10 + =C2=BD your character level + your Wis modifier), in additi=
on to dealing damage normally. A defender who fails this saving throw is <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/conditionSummary.htm#stunned">stunned</=
a> for 1 round (until just before your next action).  A stunned creature dr=
ops everything held, can=E2=80=99t take actions, takes a -2 penalty to AC, =
and loses his Dexterity bonus to AC. You may attempt a stunning attack once=
 per day for every four levels you have attained (but see Special), and no =
more than once per round. <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/typesSubtyp=
es.htm#constructType">Constructs</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd=
/typesSubtypes.htm#oozeType">oozes</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/s=
rd/typesSubtypes.htm#plantType">plants</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.o=
rg/srd/typesSubtypes.htm#undeadType">undead</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20=
srd.org/srd/typesSubtypes.htm#incorporealSubtype">incorporeal creatures</a>=
, and creatures immune to <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/acti=
onsInCombat.htm#criticalHits">critical hits</a> cannot be stunned.
