<h3 id=3D"track">Track [General]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	To find tracks or to follow them for 1 mile requires a successful <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/survival.htm">Survival</a> check. You=
 must make another <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/survival.ht=
m">Survival</a> check every time the tracks become difficult to follow.
</p>
<p>
	You move at half your normal speed (or at your normal speed with a -5 pena=
lty on the check, or at up to twice your normal speed with a -20 penalty on=
 the check). The DC depends on the surface and the prevailing conditions, a=
s given on <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#tableTrackDC">Ta=
ble: Track DC</a>.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"verySoftGround">Very Soft Ground</h5>
<p>
	Any surface (fresh snow, thick dust, wet mud) that holds deep, clear impre=
ssions of footprints.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"softGround">Soft Ground</h5>
<p>
	Any surface soft enough to yield to pressure, but firmer than wet mud or f=
resh snow, in which a creature leaves frequent but shallow footprints.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"firmGround">Firm Ground</h5>
<p>
	Most normal outdoor surfaces (such as lawns, fields, woods, and the like) =
or exceptionally soft or dirty indoor surfaces (thick rugs and very dirty o=
r dusty floors). The creature might leave some traces (broken branches or t=
ufts of hair), but it leaves only occasional or partial footprints.
</p>

<h5 id=3D"hardGround">Hard Ground</h5>
<p>
	Any surface that doesn=E2=80=99t hold footprints at all, such as bare rock=
 or an indoor floor. Most streambeds fall into this category, since any foo=
tprints left behind are obscured or washed away. The creature leaves only t=
races (scuff marks or displaced pebbles).
</p>
<p>
	Several modifiers may apply to the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/s=
kills/survival.htm">Survival</a> check, as given on <a href=3D"https://www.=
d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#tableTrackDCModifiers">Table: Track DC Modifiers</=
a>.
</p>

<p>
	If you fail a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/survival.htm">S=
urvival</a> check, you can retry after 1 hour (outdoors) or 10 minutes (ind=
oors) of searching.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	Without this feat, you can use the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/s=
kills/survival.htm">Survival</a> skill to find tracks, but you can follow t=
hem only if the DC for the task is 10 or lower. Alternatively, you can use =
the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/search.htm">Search</a> ski=
ll to find a footprint or similar sign of a creature=E2=80=99s passage usin=
g the DCs given above, but you can=E2=80=99t use <a href=3D"https://www.d20=
srd.org/srd/skills/search.htm">Search</a> to follow tracks, even if someone=
 else has already found them.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm">ranger</a> aut=
omatically has Track as a bonus feat. He need not select it.
</p>
<p>
	This feat does not allow you to find or follow the tracks made by a subjec=
t of a <a class=3D"spell" href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/spells/passWit=
houtTrace.htm">pass without trace</a> spell.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"trample">Trample [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/skills/ride.htm">Ride</a> 1 rank, <a=
 href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#mountedCombat">Mounted Combat=
</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When you attempt to <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAt=
tacks.htm#overrun">overrun</a> an opponent while mounted, your target may n=
ot choose to avoid you. Your mount may make one hoof attack against any tar=
get you knock down, gaining the standard +4 bonus on <a href=3D"https://www=
.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm#attackRoll">attack rolls</a> ag=
ainst <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/conditionSummary.htm#prone">pro=
ne</a> targets.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Trample as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"twoWeaponDefense">Two-Weapon Defense [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Dex 15, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#twoWeaponFighting"=
>Two-Weapon Fighting</a>.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When wielding a <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapons.ht=
m#doubleWeapons">double weapon</a> or two weapons (not including <a href=3D=
"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#naturalWeapons">natural we=
apons</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapons.htm#un=
armedStrike">unarmed strikes</a>), you gain a +1 <a href=3D"https://www.d20=
srd.org/srd/theBasics.htm#shieldBonus">shield bonus</a> to your AC.  See th=
e <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#twoWeapon=
Fighting">Two-Weapon Fighting</a> special attack.
</p>
<p>
	When you are <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/actionsInCombat.=
htm#fightingDefensivelyasaStandardAction">fighting defensively</a> or using=
 the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/actionsInCombat.htm#total=
Defense">total defense</a> action, this <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/s=
rd/theBasics.htm#shieldBonus">shield bonus</a> increases to +2.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Two-Weapon Defense as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"twoWeaponFighting">Two-Weapon Fighting [General]</h3>
<p>
	You can fight with a weapon in each hand. You can make one extra attack ea=
ch round with the second weapon.
</p>

<h5>Prerequisite</h5>
<p>
	Dex 15.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	Your penalties on <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStati=
stics.htm#attackRoll">attack rolls</a> for fighting with two weapons are re=
duced. The penalty for your primary hand lessens by 2 and the one for your =
off hand lessens by 6.  See the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/comba=
t/specialAttacks.htm#twoWeaponFighting">Two-Weapon Fighting</a> special att=
ack.
</p>

<h5>Normal</h5>
<p>
	If you wield a second weapon in your off hand, you can get one extra attac=
k per round with that weapon. When fighting in this way you suffer a -6 pen=
alty with your regular attack or attacks with your primary hand and a -10 p=
enalty to the attack with your off hand. If your off-hand weapon is light t=
he penalties are reduced by 2 each. (An <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/s=
rd/equipment/weapons.htm#unarmedStrike">unarmed strike</a> is always consid=
ered light.)
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A 2nd-level <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/ranger.htm">rang=
er</a> who has chosen the two-weapon combat style is treated as having Two-=
Weapon Fighting, even if he does not have the prerequisite for it, but only=
 when he is wearing light or no armor.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Two-Weapon Fighting as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"weaponFinesse">Weapon Finesse [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisite</h5>
<p>
	Base attack bonus +1.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	With a light weapon, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapo=
ns.htm#rapier">rapier</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/=
weapons.htm#whip">whip</a>, or <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipm=
ent/weapons.htm#chainSpiked">spiked chain</a> made for a creature of your s=
ize category, you may use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength =
modifier on <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.h=
tm#attackRoll">attack rolls</a>. If you carry a shield, its armor check pen=
alty applies to your attack rolls.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Weapon Finesse as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>
<p>
	<a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/specialAbilities.htm#naturalWeapons"=
>Natural weapons</a> are always considered light weapons.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"weaponFocus">Weapon Focus [General]</h3>
<p>
	Choose one type of weapon. You can also choose <a href=3D"https://www.d20s=
rd.org/srd/equipment/weapons.htm#unarmedStrike">unarmed strike</a> or <a hr=
ef=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#grapple">grapple=
</a> (or ray, if you are a spellcaster) as your weapon for purposes of this=
 feat.
</p>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Proficiency with selected weapon, base attack bonus +1.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You gain a +1 bonus on all <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/co=
mbatStatistics.htm#attackRoll">attack rolls</a> you make using the selected=
 weapon.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time=
 you take the feat, it applies to a new type of weapon.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Weapon Focus as one of his fighter bonus feats. He must have Weap=
on Focus with a weapon to gain the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/fe=
ats.htm#weaponSpecialization">Weapon Specialization</a> feat for that weapo=
n.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"weaponSpecialization">Weapon Specialization [General]</h3>
<p>
	Choose one type of weapon for which you have already selected the <a href=
=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#weaponFocus">Weapon Focus</a> feat=
. You can also choose <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/equipment/weapo=
ns.htm#unarmedStrike">unarmed strike</a> or <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.o=
rg/srd/combat/specialAttacks.htm#grapple">grapple</a> as your weapon for pu=
rposes of this feat. You deal extra damage when using this weapon.
</p>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Proficiency with selected weapon, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/fe=
ats.htm#weaponFocus">Weapon Focus</a> with selected weapon, <a href=3D"http=
s://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> level 4th.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You gain a +2 bonus on all damage rolls you make using the selected weapon=
.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time=
 you take the feat, it applies to a new type of weapon.
</p>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Weapon Specialization as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"whirlwindAttack">Whirlwind Attack [General]</h3>

<h5>Prerequisites</h5>
<p>
	Dex 13, Int 13, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#combatExpe=
rtise">Combat Expertise</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.ht=
m#dodge">Dodge</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#mobilit=
y">Mobility</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/feats.htm#springAtta=
ck">Spring Attack</a>, base attack bonus +4.
</p>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	When you use the <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/actionsInCom=
bat.htm#fullAttack">full attack</a> action, you can give up your regular at=
tacks and instead make one melee attack at your full base attack bonus agai=
nst each opponent within reach.
</p>
<p>
	When you use the Whirlwind Attack feat, you also forfeit any bonus or extr=
a attacks granted by other feats, spells, or abilities.
</p>

<h5>Special</h5>
<p>
	A <a href=3D"https://www.d20srd.org/srd/classes/fighter.htm">fighter</a> m=
ay select Whirlwind Attack as one of his fighter bonus feats.
</p>

<h3 id=3D"widenSpell">Widen Spell [Metamagic]</h3>

<h5>Benefit</h5>
<p>
	You can alter a burst, emanation, line, or spread shaped spell to increase=
 its area. Any numeric measurements of the spell=E2=80=99s area increase by=
 100%.A widened spell uses up a spell slot three levels higher than the spe=
ll=E2=80=99s actual level.
</p>
<p>
	Spells that do not have an area of one of these four sorts are not affecte=
d by this feat.
</p>

